258
00:17:04,607 --> 00:17:07,997
I have a teammate who recently injured his leg.

259
00:17:07,997 --> 00:17:10,927
His mom told him to stop playing football.

260
00:17:10,927 --> 00:17:13,167
But his dad?

261
00:17:13,167 --> 00:17:14,887
A different story.

262
00:17:14,887 --> 00:17:20,327
His dad thinks that kid's happiness should come first.

263
00:17:20,327 --> 00:17:23,897
Don't you agree with that?

264
00:17:24,720 --> 00:17:28,154
First, I need to know the specifics of his injury.

265
00:17:28,154 --> 00:17:29,847
Uncle Song!

266
00:17:29,847 --> 00:17:32,437
That is not the point.

267
00:17:32,437 --> 00:17:36,287
The point is that he had a fight with his own parents.

268
00:17:37,367 --> 00:17:41,477
I can't help but feel pity.

269
00:17:41,477 --> 00:17:45,647
My dad has always supported my dream.

270
00:17:45,647 --> 00:17:47,427
I thought to myself,

271
00:17:47,427 --> 00:17:53,667
if my teammate's family were the same, there'd be nothing to argue about, right?

272
00:17:53,667 --> 00:17:55,667
You too, Uncle Song.

273
00:17:55,667 --> 00:18:01,897
You always upheld your dream of becoming a doctor and achieved great things.

274
00:18:02,607 --> 00:18:04,987
Right?

275
00:18:04,987 --> 00:18:07,887
Speaking of that, I have questions for you too.

276
00:18:07,887 --> 00:18:09,127
Go ahead.

277
00:18:09,127 --> 00:18:14,817
Have you gone to Dr. Zheng for acupuncture lately?

278
00:18:15,847 --> 00:18:16,997
No.

279
00:18:16,997 --> 00:18:20,647
- Nope. 
 - We were roommates back in university.

280
00:18:20,647 --> 00:18:23,857
He told me everything about your situation.

281
00:18:24,957 --> 00:18:25,997
I'm warning you.

282
00:18:25,997 --> 00:18:31,467
If you don't take care of that old injury, you're going to suffer later.

283
00:18:31,467 --> 00:18:33,507
Come to me from now on.

284
00:18:33,507 --> 00:18:36,127
You'd go somewhere else instead of the hospital?

285
00:18:36,127 --> 00:18:39,567
What, trying to make me look like a bad doctor?

286
00:18:39,567 --> 00:18:41,277
No. It's not what I meant.

287
00:18:41,277 --> 00:18:45,277
Since you're here, get an X-ray.

288
00:18:51,667 --> 00:18:54,957
Uncle Song, my mom must never find out.

289
00:18:54,957 --> 00:18:57,617
Just go.

290
00:18:57,617 --> 00:18:59,517
Thanks, Uncle Song.

291
00:19:25,717 --> 00:19:27,427
 Coming. 

292
00:19:30,997 --> 00:19:33,037
- Cong. 
 - Huan Er?

293
00:19:33,857 --> 00:19:36,277
I brought you the books.

294
00:19:40,037 --> 00:19:42,227
Are you having dinner?

295
00:19:42,227 --> 00:19:45,717
I was going to ask you to dinner later.

296
00:19:45,717 --> 00:19:48,957
Well, join me.

297
00:19:48,957 --> 00:19:50,657
Okay.

298
00:19:55,167 --> 00:19:56,757
You're a food expert.

299
00:19:56,757 --> 00:19:58,607
You even have your own set of tools.

300
00:19:58,607 --> 00:20:00,477
Practice makes perfect.

301
00:20:00,477 --> 00:20:02,687
My mom makes it for me all the time.

302
00:20:06,197 --> 00:20:11,127
Cong, Aunt Hao has done so much for you.

303
00:20:11,127 --> 00:20:15,567
I know you care about Aunt Hao.

304
00:20:17,847 --> 00:20:23,677
As your friend, you have my full support in transferring to a regular class.

305
00:20:23,677 --> 00:20:29,927
But to truly resolve this situation, you must communicate with your parents.

306
00:20:29,927 --> 00:20:31,387
Right?

307
00:20:32,717 --> 00:20:34,757
I understand the logic.

308
00:20:34,757 --> 00:20:37,037
But my mom is...

309
00:20:41,137 --> 00:20:44,567
Anyway, I'll think about it.

310
00:20:44,567 --> 00:20:48,707
At least wait until she calms down.

311
00:20:48,707 --> 00:20:50,057
Okay.

312
00:20:50,057 --> 00:20:52,340
As long as you talk to her.

313
00:20:52,340 --> 00:20:55,127
If you need any help, feel free to ask.

314
00:20:55,127 --> 00:20:57,517
Jing Xi Chi and I will come to your rescue.

315
00:20:57,517 --> 00:21:00,347
Nothing can stop the two of us.

316
00:21:06,887 --> 00:21:08,857
Hello, Aunt Lin.

317
00:21:12,057 --> 00:21:14,757
Yeah, we were just studying together.

318
00:21:14,757 --> 00:21:18,097
Xi Chi should be home soon.

319
00:21:18,097 --> 00:21:19,717
All right.

320
00:21:21,237 --> 00:21:24,077
Sure. Bye, Aunt Lin.

321
00:21:30,517 --> 00:21:32,277
A genius indeed.

322
00:21:32,277 --> 00:21:35,367
Even your lie is genius.

323
00:21:35,367 --> 00:21:38,127
Is Jing Xi Chi playing football again?

324
00:21:38,127 --> 00:21:39,817
Definitely.

325
00:21:39,817 --> 00:21:41,927
He does extra training every weekend.

326
00:21:41,927 --> 00:21:46,757
If his mom ever finds out, he's in for some pain.

327
00:21:46,757 --> 00:21:50,217
But why is Aunt Lin against him going professional?

328
00:21:51,477 --> 00:21:53,767
Because it's tough.

329
00:21:55,037 --> 00:21:57,297
Everyone wants to get into the top schools.

330
00:21:57,297 --> 00:22:01,677
But going professional is so much harder,

331
00:22:01,677 --> 00:22:05,627
especially since he was injured before.

332
00:22:09,807 --> 00:22:14,717
In his own words, "If you love something,

333
00:22:14,717 --> 00:22:18,867
you'll accept it to hurt you and never regret it."

334
00:22:20,617 --> 00:22:25,537
It's hard to believe he'd actually say that.

335
00:22:27,987 --> 00:22:30,777
He's not as worthless as you think.

336
00:22:30,777 --> 00:22:34,137
Sometimes I think his mind is more brilliant than mine.

337
00:22:36,037 --> 00:22:38,927
I only do things I know I can manage.

338
00:22:38,927 --> 00:22:44,137
However, when I saw how Xi Chi told his dad he wanted to go professional...

339
00:22:44,137 --> 00:22:45,577
 Come on, give me another chance. 

340
00:22:45,577 --> 00:22:48,087
 Just one more time. Let me show you. 

341
00:22:48,087 --> 00:22:51,307
- He inspired me. 
  - Just let me show you. 

342
00:22:57,847 --> 00:23:00,677
So it was because of him.

343
00:23:00,677 --> 00:23:04,587
Curse you, Jing Xi Chi. You tricked me again.

344
00:23:05,957 --> 00:23:07,797
What was that?

345
00:23:09,277 --> 00:23:11,077
It's nothing.

346
00:23:15,437 --> 00:23:19,277
I just think that you both are really special.

347
00:23:19,277 --> 00:23:22,197
You grew up knowing what you like.

348
00:23:22,197 --> 00:23:23,957
You know what you want.

349
00:23:23,957 --> 00:23:26,317
Everything goes smoothly.

350
00:23:28,167 --> 00:23:29,927
But not me.

351
00:23:29,927 --> 00:23:32,987
I'm always studying without a goal.

352
00:23:32,987 --> 00:23:35,137
I'm so silly.

353
00:23:43,167 --> 00:23:45,647
Sign up for some talent courses.

354
00:23:45,647 --> 00:23:47,757
It's not too late to start.

355
00:23:47,757 --> 00:23:49,297
Talent courses?

356
00:23:49,297 --> 00:23:50,757
Yeah.

357
00:23:52,087 --> 00:23:56,127
If you're afraid of strangers, I can go with you.

358
00:23:56,127 --> 00:23:59,517
Never mind. My problem is nothing compared to yours.

359
00:23:59,517 --> 00:24:02,147
I can handle it. Thanks.

360
00:24:05,887 --> 00:24:08,587
Talent courses?

361
00:24:10,097 --> 00:24:13,077
I do envy you sometimes.

362
00:24:15,757 --> 00:24:19,067
- Did you just sayâ€” 
 - Nothing.

363
00:24:19,067 --> 00:24:20,667
Have some crabs.

364
00:24:20,667 --> 00:24:22,557
You too.

365
00:24:25,737 --> 00:24:27,237
All right.

366
00:24:27,237 --> 00:24:29,127
Calm down.

367
00:24:29,127 --> 00:24:33,757
Song Cong must be starving. You can't starve your own kid.

368
00:24:33,757 --> 00:24:36,087
I don't care.

369
00:24:36,087 --> 00:24:39,137
You should listen to what he said that night.

370
00:24:39,137 --> 00:24:43,907
After everything I did for him, he thinks I'm wrong.

371
00:24:47,167 --> 00:24:50,807
Do you remember when he was born?

372
00:24:50,807 --> 00:24:52,717
His dad left to study in Germany.

373
00:24:52,717 --> 00:24:54,577
I had to raise the kid alone.

374
00:24:54,577 --> 00:24:58,167
Did I leave my job at the provincial hospital for nothing?

375
00:24:58,167 --> 00:24:59,857
All right.

376
00:25:00,567 --> 00:25:04,067
I left the job to look after Song Cong.

377
00:25:04,067 --> 00:25:07,327
At the time, I knew his career was starting to take off.

378
00:25:07,327 --> 00:25:09,517
I said, "It's all right, I can make the sacrifice.

379
00:25:09,517 --> 00:25:12,167
I can give this family everything."

380
00:25:12,167 --> 00:25:13,517
Guess what?

381
00:25:13,517 --> 00:25:17,897
The old man spends every day in the hospital and barely comes home.

382
00:25:19,367 --> 00:25:20,757
Seriously?

383
00:25:20,757 --> 00:25:23,677
As a man, he always avoids getting involved in problems.

384
00:25:23,677 --> 00:25:29,367
When things get serious, he never takes a firm stance.

385
00:25:29,367 --> 00:25:32,140
Yes, I can totally relate to that.

386
00:25:32,140 --> 00:25:35,517
Over the years, you've been the one taking care of the family.

387
00:25:35,517 --> 00:25:37,857
You made the most sacrifices.

388
00:25:37,857 --> 00:25:39,777
Let me just say one thing.

389
00:25:39,777 --> 00:25:42,137
Let's not keep calling it a sacrifice.

390
00:25:42,137 --> 00:25:44,567
We did it for the kids because we chose to.

391
00:25:44,567 --> 00:25:46,607
We did it because we wanted to.

392
00:25:46,607 --> 00:25:48,680
That is not sacrifice.

393
00:25:48,680 --> 00:25:50,662
You're here for a free meal.

394
00:25:50,662 --> 00:25:53,677
- You talk too much. Just eat your food! 
 - Fine. Chen Lei, long time no see.

395
00:25:53,677 --> 00:25:55,477
Just eat this. Stuff your mouth.

396
00:25:55,477 --> 00:25:57,037
Whose side are you on?

397
00:25:57,037 --> 00:25:58,717
- Yeah. 
 - Calm down.

398
00:25:58,717 --> 00:26:01,097
Let's not talk about sacrifices.

399
00:26:01,097 --> 00:26:03,507
Anyway, Hao Mei, listen to me.

400
00:26:03,507 --> 00:26:05,807
Since the father and his son won't appreciate your efforts,

401
00:26:05,807 --> 00:26:07,677
we might as well cut our losses.

402
00:26:07,677 --> 00:26:09,057
Is that okay?

403
00:26:09,057 --> 00:26:11,277
Just like me. I'm not sacrificing anything.

404
00:26:11,277 --> 00:26:13,517
I want to live my own life and realize my worth.

405
00:26:13,517 --> 00:26:14,887
Yeah.

406
00:26:14,887 --> 00:26:17,167
Everything you say here is pointless.

407
00:26:17,167 --> 00:26:20,367
If you ask me, you've expected too much from Song Cong.

408
00:26:20,367 --> 00:26:22,847
He can't take it anymore. You should pay more attention.

409
00:26:22,847 --> 00:26:25,517
Quiet down.

410
00:26:25,517 --> 00:26:28,957
It may sound harsh, but it's for your own good.

411
00:26:28,957 --> 00:26:32,477
Honestly, you want Song Cong to be in the international class.

412
00:26:32,477 --> 00:26:34,197
Is that it?

413
00:26:34,197 --> 00:26:35,617
The class?

414
00:26:35,617 --> 00:26:38,297
Who told you that? I never said that.

415
00:26:38,297 --> 00:26:43,847
Unlike some parents I know, I fully respect my son's decision.

416
00:26:43,847 --> 00:26:45,707
There's nothing wrong with Song Cong.

417
00:26:45,707 --> 00:26:47,887
His only outstanding trait is being too smart.

418
00:26:47,887 --> 00:26:49,517
He can be in any class he wants.

419
00:26:49,517 --> 00:26:51,957
He is free to be in the regular class.

420
00:26:51,957 --> 00:26:55,347
As long as he wants it, I don't mind.

421
00:26:56,297 --> 00:26:58,137
See you.

422
00:26:59,187 --> 00:27:00,887
International class?

423
00:27:00,887 --> 00:27:02,237
Come now.

424
00:27:02,237 --> 00:27:04,957
- Eat up. 
 - People are so nosy.

425
00:27:22,277 --> 00:27:23,507
Dad.

426
00:27:23,507 --> 00:27:24,517
Why are you making dinner?

427
00:27:24,517 --> 00:27:26,207
Where is Mom?

428
00:27:33,087 --> 00:27:36,677
When you go to school tomorrow, finish the transfer paperwork.

429
00:27:36,677 --> 00:27:40,127
I called your homeroom teacher.

430
00:27:40,127 --> 00:27:41,237
What's wrong?

431
00:27:41,237 --> 00:27:42,887
I'm your parent too.

432
00:27:42,887 --> 00:27:45,297
I have authority too.

433
00:27:45,297 --> 00:27:49,847
Are you saying you're willing to go against Mom for my sake?

434
00:27:49,847 --> 00:27:51,427
No way.

435
00:27:52,847 --> 00:27:56,867
Actually, you should thank Li Tian's mother.

436
00:27:59,847 --> 00:28:01,477
Move aside.

437
00:28:05,807 --> 00:28:08,677
Are you cooking or operating?

438
00:28:08,677 --> 00:28:10,087
Stop if you don't want to cook.

439
00:28:10,087 --> 00:28:12,317
Go do your stitches instead.

440
00:28:16,327 --> 00:28:19,907
Well... Mom.

441
00:28:19,907 --> 00:28:23,037
I brought the books back.

442
00:28:23,037 --> 00:28:24,757
And...

443
00:28:24,757 --> 00:28:27,537
- Dad says... 
 - Yes.

444
00:28:27,537 --> 00:28:30,297
Your dad is finally acting like a good father.

445
00:28:30,297 --> 00:28:31,507
He made the decision.

446
00:28:31,507 --> 00:28:32,907
I didn't.

447
00:28:32,907 --> 00:28:34,327
I wouldn't dare.

448
00:28:34,327 --> 00:28:36,407
I don't get it.

449
00:28:36,407 --> 00:28:40,027
If you want to get transferred, why did you win first place in the contest?

450
00:28:40,027 --> 00:28:42,097
You wasted a spot.

451
00:28:42,097 --> 00:28:44,847
Well... Mr. Fu provoked me.

452
00:28:44,847 --> 00:28:46,820
I had to clap back at him.

453
00:28:46,820 --> 00:28:52,327
Besides, the contest questions were more interesting than my usual exercises.

454
00:28:52,327 --> 00:28:54,327
I can totally relate.

455
00:28:54,327 --> 00:28:56,927
Solving questions is sometimes about the thrill.

456
00:28:56,927 --> 00:28:59,037
It's hard to hold that thrill back.

457
00:28:59,037 --> 00:29:01,167
You might just get a perfect score.

458
00:29:01,167 --> 00:29:03,807
Sometimes, when I'm stitching my patients,

459
00:29:03,807 --> 00:29:08,440
I wonder how I manage to do it so neatly and so firmly.

460
00:29:08,440 --> 00:29:10,980
I'd love to do a few extra stitches just for fun.

461
00:29:22,607 --> 00:29:24,437
Your mom is mad.

462
00:29:24,437 --> 00:29:25,957
This is going to take a while.

463
00:29:25,957 --> 00:29:28,567
Go to the regular class tomorrow.

464
00:29:28,567 --> 00:29:29,847
But Dad...

465
00:29:29,847 --> 00:29:32,057
Let's listen to Mom on this.

466
00:29:32,057 --> 00:29:34,407
You fool.

467
00:29:34,407 --> 00:29:40,317
Would I make this decision without her permission, given how serious this is?

468
00:29:43,327 --> 00:29:48,777
Actually, your dad was pretty brave when he was younger.

469
00:29:48,777 --> 00:29:50,867
But now...

470
00:29:51,987 --> 00:29:54,237
This is why I support your decision.

471
00:29:54,237 --> 00:29:59,977
Cherish your single life and the freedom you have now.

472
00:30:16,327 --> 00:30:17,887
- Up ahead! 
 - Come, center!

473
00:30:17,887 --> 00:30:19,747
- Intercept! 
 - Keep an eye on them!

474
00:30:19,747 --> 00:30:21,960
Pass it here!

475
00:30:21,960 --> 00:30:23,337
Over here!

476
00:30:23,337 --> 00:30:25,177
Jing Xi Chi!

477
00:30:27,087 --> 00:30:28,587
Come here.

478
00:30:29,437 --> 00:30:30,927
Watch them.

479
00:30:30,927 --> 00:30:32,847
Pass it to me.

480
00:30:32,847 --> 00:30:34,507
Why are you here?

481
00:30:34,507 --> 00:30:36,027
Why isn't your dear Cong with you?

482
00:30:36,027 --> 00:30:38,427
He is not my dear Cong.

483
00:30:39,237 --> 00:30:42,467
He wanted to get transferred because of what you said.

484
00:30:42,467 --> 00:30:44,037
Drop the act.

485
00:30:44,037 --> 00:30:48,097
I came to tell you he didn't make the decision because of me.

486
00:30:48,097 --> 00:30:51,417
He made up his mind after seeing the effort you put into football.

487
00:30:53,277 --> 00:30:56,127
No wonder.

488
00:30:56,127 --> 00:31:00,287
After all, I'm destined to be a spiritual leader.

489
00:31:01,437 --> 00:31:04,027
You could make a decision because of me too.

490
00:31:04,027 --> 00:31:06,517
I can guarantee your success.

491
00:31:08,437 --> 00:31:10,617
What guarantee?

492
00:31:13,197 --> 00:31:15,987
Is Song Cong really transferring?

493
00:31:22,617 --> 00:31:25,327
Turns out Aunt Hao is all bark and no bite.

494
00:31:25,327 --> 00:31:26,427
Dad.

495
00:31:26,427 --> 00:31:29,757
When I went to Song Cong's house for dinner, I was worried about him.

496
00:31:29,757 --> 00:31:33,237
I thought he was going to starve forever.

497
00:31:36,507 --> 00:31:40,617
My precious girl has been through so many ads.

498
00:31:40,617 --> 00:31:42,197
I'll leave in a few days.

499
00:31:42,197 --> 00:31:43,647
Who knows when I'll be back?

500
00:31:43,647 --> 00:31:47,047
Don't you want to see me more often?

501
00:31:48,027 --> 00:31:52,057
Yeah. I'm watching you with my eyes wide open.

502
00:31:52,057 --> 00:31:53,307
- Fine. Enough. 
 - Not yet.

503
00:31:53,307 --> 00:31:55,507
Okay, you can stop now. This is getting creepy.

504
00:31:55,507 --> 00:31:59,237
- Cut it out. Read your ads. 
 - More! Nope.

505
00:31:59,237 --> 00:32:01,857
I'll seal away this evil spirit!

506
00:32:01,857 --> 00:32:03,677
We ran out of oranges. I'll go and get some.

507
00:32:03,677 --> 00:32:05,677
Okay.

508
00:32:05,677 --> 00:32:08,477
What is this? Wilderness survival?

509
00:32:09,197 --> 00:32:11,277
Haven't decided on anything yet?

510
00:32:11,277 --> 00:32:13,207
Nope.

511
00:32:14,037 --> 00:32:19,457
Your grandpa didn't even take this long to pick a son-in-law.

512
00:32:20,197 --> 00:32:22,537
I want to try something new.

513
00:32:22,537 --> 00:32:25,667
I have to pick the right one. I'll take my time.

514
00:32:25,667 --> 00:32:27,997
Give me a break.

515
00:32:29,477 --> 00:32:35,517
Are you trying to catch up to Song Cong after seeing how ambitious he was?

516
00:32:37,607 --> 00:32:40,537
I bet you won't get it.

517
00:32:43,087 --> 00:32:46,427
Jing Xi Chi is quite ambitious too.

518
00:33:04,817 --> 00:33:07,417
 He's not as worthless as you think. 

519
00:33:54,037 --> 00:33:55,327
Chen Huan Er, hurry up!

520
00:33:55,327 --> 00:33:56,867
- I have a match to watch tonight! 
 - Coming.

521
00:33:56,867 --> 00:33:58,887
- At this rate, I'll miss the match! 
 - Wait for me.

522
00:33:58,887 --> 00:34:00,757
Hurry up!

523
00:34:07,507 --> 00:34:10,047
What is taking you so long?

524
00:34:13,067 --> 00:34:15,597
Come on. It's taking forever to tie your shoelaces.

525
